## 3. Strength Level Tiers (Classification)

Use a percentile-based tier system. These tier names and percentile cut-offs are a generic,
widely-used convention (not proprietary).

| Tier | Percentile | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| **Beginner** | ≥ 5th | Stronger than 5% of lifters |
| **Novice** | ≥ 20th | Stronger than 20% |
| **Intermediate** | ≥ 50th | Stronger than 50% (population median) |
| **Advanced** | ≥ 80th | Stronger than 80% |
| **Elite** | ≥ 95th | Stronger than 95% |

**How to assign a tier:** Compute the user's estimated 1RM, normalize for bodyweight (and optionally
age), then compare against the percentile distribution for that exercise/gender/bodyweight cohort
(built from the dataset in Section 7). The percentile the user falls into → their tier.

