## 5. Bodyweight-Adjusted Scoring (Powerlifts: Squat + Bench + Deadlift)

These let users compare across bodyweights and genders. All are public formulas.
**Bodyweight `x` and all lifts must be in KILOGRAMS.** Total = squat + bench + deadlift (kg).

### 5.1 Wilks (Original / 2004)
```
Coefficient = 500 / (a + b·x + c·x² + d·x³ + e·x⁴ + f·x⁵)
Wilks Score = Total(kg) × Coefficient
```
| Const | Men | Women |
|---|---|---|
| a | -216.0475144 | 594.31747775582 |
| b | 16.2606339 | -27.23842536447 |
| c | -0.002388645 | 0.82112226871 |
| d | -0.00113732 | -0.00930733913 |
| e | 7.01863e-6 | 4.731582e-5 |
| f | -1.291e-8 | -9.054e-8 |

### 5.2 Wilks-2 (2020 revision)
Same equation form, updated constants:
| Const | Men | Women |
|---|---|---|
| a | 47.46178854 | -125.4255398 |
| b | 8.472061379 | 13.71219419 |
| c | 0.07369410346 | -0.03307250631 |
| d | -0.001395833811 | -0.001050400051 |
| e | 7.07665973070743e-6 | 9.38773881462799e-6 |
| f | -1.20804336482315e-8 | -2.3334613884954e-8 |

### 5.3 DOTS (2019, Tim Konertz)
4th-degree polynomial; widely considered the most neutral across bodyweights.
```
Coefficient = 500 / (A + B·x + C·x² + D·x³ + E·x⁴)
DOTS Score = Total(kg) × Coefficient
```
| Const | Men | Women |
|---|---|---|
| A | -307.75076 | -57.96288 |
| B | 24.0900756 | 13.6175032 |
| C | -0.1918759221 | -0.1126655495 |
| D | 0.0007391293 | 0.0005158568 |
| E | -0.000001093 | -0.0000010706 |

> Verify the DOTS constants against the source repo (Section 7) on first build — different sites
> publish them in different sign conventions / orderings. The polynomial is written here highest
> term last (constant first).

### 5.4 Score interpretation (rough, both formulas)

| Wilks/DOTS | Level |
|---|---|
| < 200 | Beginner |
| 200–300 | Intermediate |
| 300–400 | Advanced |
| 400–500 | Elite |
| 500+ | World class |

**References:** Wilks R., Powerlifting Australia (1995, rev. 2020); Konertz T., BVDK (2019);
Vanderburgh & Batterham on allometric strength normalization.

